{\f8\fs28\b\i0\outl Phone Assistance\par }{\f8\fs56\b\i0 CalFresh\par }\pard\plain \s5\f8\fs20\ltrpar\qj\fi0\li0\ri0\sb40\sa80\facenter\sl240\slmult0\expnd0\expndtw0\cf0\up0\charscalex100\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\accnone\hyphpar1\lang1033
{\fs20 CalFresh (formerly called Food Stamps) is a government program that provides benefits so that you and your family will not go hungry. If you are eligible, you get an Electronic Benefit Transfer (EBT) card that you can use to buy food at most stores. CalFresh is free but you must apply for them. \par Many people don\rquote t know they qualify or do not know how to apply. If you need food, you should apply.  Everyone has the right to apply and deserves to have enough to eat. \par You can use your CalFresh card at (to find a retailer near you that welcomes SNAP EBT customers, visit http://www.snapretailerlocator.com):\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
Almost every food store\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?Many Farmer's Markets\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?Some meals-on-wheels programs\par \'95\u8239 ?
Some shelters are authorized to take CalFresh as payment from clients\par You can use it to purchase:\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?Any food item except hot foods that are meant to be eaten immediately\par \'95\u8239 ?
Seeds to grow your own food. \par \'95\u8239 ?CalFresh cannot be used for non-food products such as soap or diapers. \par \par \par \par Each month you get a dollar amount  deposited into your EBT card to help you buy food. The amount your household will  receive depends on your income and other factors. \par  \par \par \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 1. General Eligibility }{\fs20 \par You must meet the program\rquote s income limits. In order to see if you qualify, visit www.calfresh.ca.gov/PG841.htm and see \ldblquote How Do I Apply for CalFresh\rdblquote  on page 12. You don\rquote t have to have a home, or a place to cook, or a permanent address to get CalFresh. You can also own a home and/or car and still be eligible for CalFresh.  \par }
\pard\plain \s5\f8\fs20\ltrpar\qj\fi0\li0\ri0\sb40\sa80\facenter\sl240\slmult0\expnd0\expndtw0\cf0\up0\charscalex100\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\accnone\hyphpar1\lang1033
{\fs20 Some persons do not qualify:\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?SSI/SSP recipients in California cannot get CalFresh because a food allowance is included in the SSI grant. \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
 Some non-citizens legally in the United States can get CalFresh (see page 58 Guide for Non-Citizens\rdblquote  ). Even if you are not eligible for this reason, other adults or children living in your home may be eligible and should apply. Your immigration status will not be affected if other family members use nutrition programs like CalFresh.\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
If you were convicted of a felony for sales or manufacturing of drugs after August 22, 1996, you will be permanently ineligible for CalFresh.  If your felony was for possession or use of drugs, you can get CalFresh if you show that you are in a drug recovery program, or have completed one OR are on a waiting list for one, or sign an affidavit that you are no longer using drugs.\par \'95    You can be permanently disqualified from the program if you are caught selling CalFresh benefits worth over $500. \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
Strikers and their families are usually kept out of the program, unless they meet the income limits before the strike.\par }{\f8\fs20\b\i0
2. Special Rules for Students }{\fs20 \par Students between the ages of 18 and 49 who are enrolled at least half-time in a program of higher education can get CalFresh if they meet ANY of the following: \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
\tab Enrolled in CalWORKs \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\tab Working and getting paid at least 20 hours per week, or an average of 80 hours per month \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
\tab Receiving or eligible for a work-study grant \par \'95 \tab A full-time student with a child under 12 \par \'95\tab A part-time student with a child under 6 or between the ages of 6 and 12 with no adequate childcare available   \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
\tab \u8239 ?In a government approved job training program\par \'95\tab Not planning to register for the next normal school term \par If the student doesn\rquote t meet any one of these requirements, the other people in the home may still get CalFresh even though the student can\rquote t. \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 3. \ldblquote Households\rdblquote  }{\fs20 \par The term \ldblquote household\rdblquote  has special meaning in the CalFresh Program. It does not mean you have a house. A household can be one person who lives alone, or it can be a group of persons, related or unrelated, who live in the same place. There is no limit to the number of \ldblquote households\rdblquote  that can be in the same home. A \ldblquote household\rdblquote   includes those who buy and prepare their own food together. \par Some relatives who live together must be included in the same household, even if they do NOT buy and prepare their meals together.  These are:\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
Your immediate family\'97you, your spouse, your children age 21 and under \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?Your parents and you (unless you are over 21) \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
Those who are acting as parents for a child under 18, unless the child is in foster care. \par Relatives who CAN be considered  separate households even if they live in the same place include:\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
Parents living with their adult children (over 21) \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?Adult brothers and sisters.    \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 4. Income Limits }{\fs20 \par }{\f8\fs20\b\i0 Gross income limit: }{\fs20  You can have an income and get CalFresh if the household\rquote s \ldblquote gross income\rdblquote  or total income before taxes is below certain limits. If anyone in your household is disabled or over 60 years old, this limit does not apply to you and you should consider applying if you are having trouble purchasing food and are not receiving SSI/SSP.   \par Income that doesn\rquote t count includes:\par }
