{\fs20 \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?Money earned by children under age 18 if they are in school at least half-time \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
Money paid for you to a third party by someone who is not legally obligated to pay you, (for example if your grandparent pays your rent directly to the landlord)\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
Most loans\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?Federal payments to help you with utilities\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
\ldblquote Earned Income Tax Credit\rdblquote  for one full year after you get it\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
CalWORKs homeless assistance \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?Foster care payments (when the foster children are not part of the household) \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
