{\f8\fs20\b\i0 1. Emergency CalFresh Benefits}{\fs20 \par You may be eligible to get CalFresh the same day or at most within 3 days if one of the following applies:\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
The cost of your rent/mortgage payment or utilities is more than your monthly income and cash-on-hand. \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
Your liquid resources are less than the gross income requirements.\par To apply for emergency CalFresh, you need to do the application and check the box that says you want expedited CalFresh. The worker will ask for your proof of identity, residence, income, and resources, but you cannot be denied for not having these documents with you. \par There are many ways to prove your identity, including your driver\rquote s license, a sworn statement, a phone call to someone who knows you, a library card, or a letter addressed to you. \par If your case is approved, an EBT card and PIN number will be issued no later than the third calendar day after you apply so you can access your food stamp benefits. If the third day falls on a weekend or holiday, you have the right to receive your CalFresh on that Friday. If you apply after the 15th you will get the CalFresh for that month and your next month\rquote s CalFresh. \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 2. Non Emergency }{\fs20 \par }{\f8\fs20\b\i0 Application: }{\fs20 You have the right to apply in your own language and to turn in a written application on the day you go in. If someone tells you to come back to submit the application, you may insist on filing an application that same day.  \par It is best to fill out the application form as completely as you can, but you only need to fill out your name, address and signature to file an application. Once you turn in your application, you will be given an interview with an eligibility worker.\par You can call (916) 874-2072 to have an application mailed to you; fill it out and send it in by mail, or have someone else turn it in for you. You will still have to be interviewed either by phone or in the office depending on your situation. Phone interviews can be scheduled to make it easier for you to finish the application.  \par You can also apply online at www.mybenefitscalwin.org.\par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 Interview: }{\fs20  You may bring someone along to help you. You may be asked to sign a form making them your \ldblquote authorized representative,\rdblquote  but you do not have to. You will go over the application you filled out and will be asked for additional information. \par You should be given a list of documents that you will need to complete the application process. You may be given ten days to turn in the documents. If you do not have all the necessary documents, you or someone you know may sign a statement explaining why not. \par You may be able to receive benefits while you continue to gather the required information. The eligibility worker should help you get some of your missing papers.\par If everyone in your household is disabled or over 60 years of age you may request either that an eligibility worker be sent to your home at a time you agree to or that you be interviewed by phone. A worker may also visit or phone you if no adult in your household can go to the office for good reasons such as illness or disability. \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 Next steps: }{\fs20  If you are asked to mail additional papers to the County office, ask the worker for a stamped envelope addressed to him or her. If you take in papers, get a receipt. \par Keep your own copy of all the paperwork. If you need help and your worker is not available, the worker of the day or a supervisor should help you.  \par Within 30 days of applying, the County office must either mail you an EBT card and PIN number and a notice of approval or inform you in writing that you do not qualify and the reason why not. \par If you are denied CalFresh, and believe you are eligible, request a hearing or call a legal aid organization right away. (see page 70 \ldblquote Good Advice.\rdblquote )\par \par \par \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 1. Quarterly Reports }{\fs20 \par As of August 2013, you only have to report every six months. The form is called SAR-7. THIS IS EXTREMELY IMPORTANT!  You will be asked to report your income, property and household composition, and any changes in your income, property or household composition that you anticipate in the next three months. You will need to fill it out in order to continue to be eligible. Under certain circumstances, you must report changes before your required reporting month.\par }
\pard\plain \s5\f8\fs20\ltrpar\qj\fi0\li0\ri0\sb40\sa80\facenter\sl240\slmult0\expnd0\expndtw0\cf0\up0\charscalex100\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\accnone\hyphpar1\lang1033
{\fs20 If your SAR-7 gets lost, or you do not turn it in, your case will be suspended at the end of the month. If you had a good reason, such as being sick or not receiving the form in the mail, your worker may grant you \ldblquote good cause\rdblquote  and your benefits may be restored.  You have up to 30 days after your report due date to turn in your report to have your benefits reinstated regardless of whether or not you had a \ldblquote good cause\rdblquote  for not turning in your report on time.   \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 2. Recertification}{\fs20 \par You must be reviewed for benefits each year before the end of your certification period or your CalFresh will be cut off. You will receive a letter that tells you the application for this review is due. Be sure to complete this on time so you can continue to receive CalFresh without a break. \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 3. Work Registration }{\fs20 \par All CalFresh household members age 16 through age 59 who do not have children in the home must be screened for work registration.  This may or may not be required, and is contingent upon state unemployment levels. \par If you are not found to be exempt, you must agree to: \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
Respond to a request of additional information regarding employment status or availability for employment \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
Report to a suitable job if referred \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ? Accept a suitable job offer\par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?
Not voluntarily reduce work hours to less than 30 hours per week \par \'95\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?\u8239 ?Cooperate with the requirements of any welfare-to-work program you are assigned to, including CalFresh "workfare"\par In CalFresh workfare, the number of hours you do is based on the amount of your CalFresh benefits divided by minimum wage. Sometimes when unemployment is high the County may not require workfare.\par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 Fair Hearing }{\fs20 \par Everyone has the right to a \ldblquote fair hearing\rdblquote  if you feel you were unfairly denied or to correct any mistakes (see pg 67.) If you appeal within 10 days or up to the day the action takes effect (whichever period of time is longer), your usual benefits will continue until the matter is resolved.\par \par \par \par \par }
