{\f8\fs28\b\i0\outl What Are The Benefits?   \par }{\f8\fs56\b\i0 Child Nutrition \par }{\f8\fs28\b\i0\outl Can My Child Get Free School Breakfast and Lunch?     \par }
\pard\plain \s5\f8\fs20\ltrpar\qj\fi0\li0\ri0\sb40\sa80\facenter\sl240\slmult0\expnd0\expndtw0\cf0\up0\charscalex100\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\accnone\hyphpar1\lang1033
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 All low-income children }{\fs20 qualify for free or reduced price school meals, regardless of immigration status. Children who eat regular meals learn better and are usually sick less than other children. All public schools and some private and parochial schools offer breakfast and lunch programs. \par Your child qualifies for free or reduced-price meals if your gross family income per month (income before taxes or deductions) is below a certain level. \par }
{\fs20 You should be given an application for the meal program in your own language at the beginning of the school year or whenever your child transfers. You can also ask for one at any time from the school office, because if your income goes down during the year, your child may become eligible.\par If you receive CalWORKs, food stamps, or the Food Distribution Program on Indian Reservations, the only information you have to give is your case number, and your child automatically qualifies for free meals. \par If you do not receive CalWORKs or food stamps, you will have to list the total income of your household, the names of household members, and the Social Security number of the adult signing the application. If you do not have a number, just write \ldblquote none\rdblquote . You are not required to apply for a number or give a reason for not having one. \par In some cases, you must give the school some proof of your income (by showing your pay stubs to the school secretary, for example). All information gathered is confidential and cannot be given to other government agencies. \par If the information you give on the application shows that you qualify, your child can begin receiving free or reduced-price meals immediately. \par Foster children are often eligible for free meals, regardless of the foster parents\rquote  income. \par }
