{\f8\fs20\b0\i0 General Assistance (GA) is a program for people who have almost no money at all and don\rquote t qualify for unemployment benefits, CalWORKs or Social Security Programs. GA has a lot of rules and doesn\rquote t provide much money .}
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 \par 1. Residence }{\fs20 \par To qualify for GA, you must reside in Sacramento County for at least 15 days and intend to remain here. \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 2. Cash and Resource Limits }{\fs20 \par You cannot have more than a certain amount in cash or in a bank account when you apply. However, you can own the following resources, as long as they do not exceed the maximum limits. For current limits, visit http://www.dha.saccounty.net/benefits/Pages/default.aspx#ga or call (916) 874-2063. \par \'95 Car(s)\par \'95\u8239 ?
Personal property\par \'95\u8239 ?Necessary household furnishings and tools and supplies needed for rehabilitation or self-sufficiency.\par \'95\u8239 ?
The house you live in.\par If you live with your spouse, his or her income will be counted in deciding if you are eligible, unless your spouse receives SSI. \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 3. Time Limits }{\fs20 \par If you are able to work, DHA will classify you as \ldblquote employable.\rdblquote   If you are \ldblquote employable,\rdblquote  you can only receive GA for 3 months in any 12-month period. \par If you are unable to work, DHA will classify you as \ldblquote unemployable\rdblquote  and you will not have a time limit.\par \par \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 1. Basic Benefits}{\fs20 \par GA benefits provide monthly cash aid in Sacramento County. In addition to the cash aid, a bus pass is provided. \par Once approved, you can earn up to money each month with no loss of benefits. \par Go to the DHA office to apply for GA. Not all DHA offices take GA applications. (see pg. 68 for DHA Offices).\par Be prepared for a long day, but remember that you have the right to apply. Tell the worker at DHA that you need GA. You will have to fill out an application. Bring with you identification and papers that prove your income, resources and citizenship (your birth certificate is best but other documents can work). If you are an immigrant bring documents that indicate your status.\par \par Every GA applicant has a right to request \ldblquote expedited\rdblquote  CalFesh (food stamps) (see pg. 13 - Emergency Food Stamps).\par If you are eligible, DHA must issue you food stamps within three days of your application if you are eligible to receive expedited food stamps. \par Make sure that your worker has a good address for you; otherwise, you may miss important notices from DHA. Your home address and mailing address do not have to be the same.  If you are homeless, you can use the DHA address to pick up your mail,  but if you do, you must check your mail once a week. Some community organizations and shelters provide free mail service. \par You must be helped if you are in the office before it closes. If you need help immediately, you should receive it. If anyone does not let you apply or tells you to come back the next day, insist on speaking to a worker, and then a supervisor, and then the deputy director, if necessary.\par The county has 30 calendar days to approve your case and issue you GA benefits. Your benefits will be issued to you on an Electronic Benefits Transfer (\ldblquote EBT\rdblquote ) card.   When your EBT card is issued to you, you will also select a personal identification number (\ldblquote PIN\rdblquote ).  Using your EBT card and your PIN, you can access your benefits through any ATM. Your DHA worker should provide you with a list of ATMs in the area.  This list will let you know which ATMs are free and which ones charge a fee.\par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 2. If You Think You Are Unable to Work}{\fs20 \par If you are disabled you may want to apply for SSI first (see pg. 26 - SSI). You may apply for GA while you wait on SSI. You can ask the county to help you apply for SSI. If you get GA because you are unemployable you must apply for SSI.\par If you are disabled, apply for GA as \ldblquote unemployable\rdblquote . You should bring any medications, prescriptions, private doctor\rquote s statement, or other proof about your disability.  \par }
\pard\plain \s5\f8\fs20\ltrpar\qj\fi0\li0\ri0\sb40\sa80\facenter\sl240\slmult0\expnd0\expndtw0\cf0\up0\charscalex100\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\accnone\hyphpar1\lang1033
{\fs20 If DHA decides that you can work, you can appeal. \par Make sure you go to all appointments because you may be denied GA if you don\rquote t.\par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 3. If You Need Special Assistance}{\fs20  \par DHA must help if you need it. If you cannot read or write, they must help you with their forms. If you have a mental disability, they must refer you to a mental health worker for evaluation. The evaluation can establish you as a Needs Special Assistance (\ldblquote NSA\rdblquote ) recipient.  NSA recipients are approved for GA promptly.  In addition, \ldblquote NSA\rdblquote  participants are protected from some sanctions, work and other program requirements, and denials of aid.\par If you request an evaluation by a mental health worker, but do not get one, you may demand that you be classified as \ldblquote medically unemployable\rdblquote  for 30 days. You will be exempt from work requirements until you get a mental health evaluation. \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 4. Emergency Money}{\fs20 \par If you have an emergency you may be able to get some money right away. This is called \ldblquote immediate need.\rdblquote   Ask DHA about this. If they do not help you, call Legal Services (pg. 70).\par \par  \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 1. If You Are Able to Work \par }{\f8\fs20\b0\i0 I}{\fs20 f you are employable, you will be required to attend job training. \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 2. If You Are Classified \ldblquote Unemployable\rdblquote }{\fs20 \par If DHA says you are disabled, you will not need to go to job training  When you are no longer disabled, you will need to go to job training and your GA will be limited to 3 months in each 12-month period. \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 3. Reports }{\fs20 \par You are required to report all changes within five (5) days. In addition, you must fill out a QR-7 report every third month. THIS IS EXTREMELY IMPORTANT! On the quarterly report, you will be asked to report your income, property and household composition.  You will also be required to report any changes in your income, property or household composition. \par If you get the form in the mail, you must fill it out and return it to the DHA office by the 5th day of the month. You should get a report form before or on the first day of the month. If you don\rquote t get it in the mail, you may call the automated phone system at (916) 874-3100 to request a form be mailed, or go to the DHA office to complete the form. \par }
\pard\plain \s5\f8\fs20\ltrpar\qj\fi0\li0\ri0\sb36\sa72\facenter\sl240\slmult0\expnd0\expndtw0\cf0\up0\charscalex100\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\accnone\hyphpar1\lang1033
{\fs20 Make sure to get a receipt showing the time and date you submitted the form. If your QR-7 gets lost, or you do not turn it in, your case will be terminated at the end of the month. }
{\fs18 \par }{\f8\fs18\b\i0 1. Hearings }{\fs18 \par }{\fs20 If your case is going to be terminated or your benefits are reduced, you have a right to a GA hearing. You must request the hearing within 10 days of the action. The County must hand-issue you a \ldblquote Notice of Action\rdblquote  seven (7) days before a hearing or 8 days if mailed. The date and time of the hearing will appear on the notice. Your benefits cannot be cut off or reduced without a hearing unless you do not go to the hearing (see Pg. 62 \ldblquote Hearings and Complaints\rdblquote ).\par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 2. Penalties}{\fs20 \par If you do not go to your GA hearing, or you lose your GA hearing, your case will be terminated (with or without a sanction) or your benefits will be reduced. If you receive a sanction and you have not been sanctioned in the past 365 days you can re-apply at once. If this is the second sanction in a year, you can re-apply in 30 days. After the third penalty in a year, you have to wait 60 days to re-apply. \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 3. If You Begin to Get SSI}{\fs20 \par GA is a \ldblquote loan\rdblquote  from the county.  If you begin to receive SSI, the amount you received on GA will be automatically deducted from your first SSI check. \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 4. After Time Limits}{\fs20 \par If your General Assistance is stopped due to the time limits: \par \'95 You can continue to get food stamps.\par \'95 You can continue to receive free and low cost health care under the Affordable Care Act.\par If you become \ldblquote unemployable\rdblquote  while you are timed off of GA, reapply for GA and provide verification that you are \ldblquote unemployable.\rdblquote  If they find you are unemployable, you will be eligible to once again receive GA and you will not be subject to time limits. Bring proof of unemployability with you to your assessment meeting. \par \par \par }
