{\fs20 \par Low income residents in Sacramento can get help with bus tickets in the following ways:\par }{\f8\fs20\b\i0 1)     Department of Human Assistance (DHA)}
{\fs20  \'96 DHA will provide an RT monthly pass  to General Assistance participants. CalWorks recipients can get money for transportation to and from their welfare to work assignment.\par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 2)     Francis House }{\fs20 \'96 Francis House provides bus tokens, gas vouchers, help obtaining birth certificates, California IDs and drivers licenses necessary to obtain jobs. 1422 C Street  Sacramento, CA 95814-0916. Phone; (916) 443-2646\par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 3)     Volunteers of America}{\fs20  \'96 purchases tickets and distributes them based on their own criteria. See pg. 6 for different locations serving families and singles.\par Discount fares are available on the RT bus lines. \par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 Seniors (age 62 and over)}{\fs20  \'96 For ndividuals with disabilities and Medicare cardholders, proof of identification is required upon boarding, and can include an RT senior or Disabled photo ID card, a Senior or Disabled photo ID card issued by another transit agency, a driver\rquote s license, a State of California ID card, a passport or identification card issued by any governmental entity containing a photo of the cardholder (and also showing verification of agefor Seniors only). Attendants of individuals with disabilities may ride for the Discount fare if possessing an RT Disabled photo ID card with an Attendant eligibility notation.\par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 Super Senior (age 75+) }{\fs20 - Proof of age verification is required to purchase a Super Senior monthly sticker. The Super Senior monthly sticker is only available for purchase at RT\rquote s Customer Service and Sales Center located at 1225 R Street.\par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 Students (age 5 - 18)}{\fs20  - To qualify, you must be pursuing a high school diploma. You will be eligible to purchase RT monthly student stickers with an RT Student photo ID card. RT Student stickers must be affixed to an RT Student photo ID card, not a school ID. Students are eligible to purchase single fares and daily passes with their school ID.\par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 Class Pass }{\fs20 - RT offers the Class Pass, which permits unlimited use for groups traveling during the hours of 9 a.m.-3:30 p.m. The Class Pass is available to any group with 10 or more students who are pursuing a high school diploma. The cost of the Class Pass is $2.50 for each student and $5 for each accompanying adult. To ensure that you have the most current price, visit www.sacrt.com/farecategories.stm or call  (916) 321-BUSS (2877). \par RT Customer Service Representatives are available to answer questions about your group travel.\par Please call RT at 321-BUSS (2877) at least 10 working days before your day of travel. RT photo ID cards are only available at RT\rquote s Photo Identification Center located at 1225 R Street, Sacramento 95811, in the Customer Service and Sales Center.\par 1}
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 . Low Cost Car Insurance}{\fs20 \par Low income drivers in Sacramento County can purchase special auto insurance for at a discounted rate. Call (800) 622-0954 to find the agent nearest you from the California Automobile Assigned Risk Plan (CAARP.) You must verify your income with tax returns and also show a valid driver\rquote s license, current vehicle registration, and proof of ownership of vehicle. \par To be eligible you must live in Sacramento County; you must be at least 19 years old and have been driving for at least 3 years without losing your license. An agent will determine if you meet the income and car requirements to qualify for CAARP.  \par Also, in the last 3 years you cannot have:\par \'95 Been responsible for an accident involving bodily injury or death \par \'95\u8239 ?
Had more than one property damage accident in which you were at fault \par \'95\u8239 ?More than one point for a moving violation \par You also cannot be a college student claimed as a dependent on someone else\rquote s taxes.\par }
{\f8\fs20\b\i0 2. Help With Smog Check}{\fs20 \par }{\fs20\cf2\outl0 The State\rquote s Consumer Assistance Program (CAP) provides financial assistance for low income consumers whose vehicles don\rquote t pass smog check. If you qualify they can help pay for repairs that will allow your car to pass. You must pay a copayment. The program is limited to available funds. Call the Department of Consumer Affairs (800) 952-5210 for information and to apply. Don\rquote t do any repairs until you are notified that you\rquote ve been approved.\par }
